commandOnAllFiles.commands.markdownDescription:
Named commands available to `commandOnAllFiles.applyOnWorkspace`.

Each **key** is a human-readable description that identifies the command in keybindings (`"args": ["My Key"]`) and the Command Palette picker. Each **value** configures what to run and which files to target.

All file-filtering properties (`includeFileExtensions`, `includeFiles`, `excludeFiles`, `excludeFolders`, `includeFolders`, `saveFiles`) are optional and override the corresponding global settings when present.

Example:
```json
"commandOnAllFiles.commands": {
  "Format TypeScript": {
    "command": "editor.action.formatDocument",
    "includeFileExtensions": [".ts", ".tsx"],
    "label": "$(file-code) Format TypeScript",
    "detail": "Runs editor.action.formatDocument on all .ts/.tsx files"
  },
  "Organise Imports": {
    "command": "editor.action.organizeImports",
    "includeFileExtensions": [".ts"],
    "saveFiles": false
  }
}
```
